The paper deals with the analysis and construction of hash families for cuckoo hashing, which is a data structure used in computer science for efficient hash table operations. This falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.DM). The paper also utilizes graph counting arguments, which is a technique commonly used in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses the evaluation time of the hash functions, which could fall under numerical analysis (cs.NA).
